						<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6c6e53c16588430f386270938fbcb888?s=42&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6c6e53c16588430f386270938fbcb888?s=84&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-42 photo' height='42' width='42' />						<b class="fn">Dario</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://scottbot.net/topic-modeling-for-humanists-a-guided-tour/#comment-169">
							<time datetime="2013-10-18T07:07:27+00:00">
								October 18, 2013 at 7:07 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>&#8220;as yet I know of no really simple implementation of topic modeling.&#8221;<br />
There is one software implementing topic modeling entirely on a GUI. However it is a commercial software, and for an educational license you need to get more than 600$ out of your pockets. The software is T-Lab (www.tlab.it/en), and among several other things it implements topic modeling using LDA and Gibbs.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://scottbot.net/topic-modeling-for-humanists-a-guided-tour/?replytocom=169#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-169", "169", "respond", "19113" )' aria-label='Reply to Dario'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
